	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yep, this item was pretty much the booby prize in the werewolf event.  But some nice monk items did drop, even for higher level monks.  The shoulder item especially (fine silken mantle); it's better than a wu's fighting mantle.  But I lost out on getting it (which I've think I've stated in too many posts now, so this is the last time!) because when it was shouted out that it dropped, the corpse was on the eastern end of the zone, and I was clear over by the Kithicor zone, I had no chance on getting to it first, especially without SoW.  Oh well, no sour grapes or anything.  Good ear items for monks are hard to find, but this is going in the trash as soon as I can acquire or afford to buy a pair of cougar claws.<br><br>By the way, this item isn't quite the utter crap people make it out to be.  People love the cougar claws, and pay around 300pp for them, and this is almost as good.  Look at the math:<br><br>Scratched Electrum Hoop +1str +4ac = Cougar Claw Earring<br><br>Scratched Electrum Hoop +1str +3ac +15hp -2dex = Orc Fang Earring<br><br>See, it's not great, but it's not THAT bad.<br>&nbsp;<br>Troodon, AKA Zararazu, Level 39 Iksar Monk, Jaggedpine Defender, Solusek Ro</td></tr>
